
Pre-bake a piecrust.

Then whisk together.

1 cup milk
1 cup brown sugar
3 eggs
1 tbl flour
1/2 cup finely chopped pecans
pinch salt
 
Pour mixture into a saucepan. Heat, stirring on  low, 'ill it just starts to thicken.
Pour the mixture into the, now cooled, piecrust.
Possible dot the top with whole pecans?
Bake 350 doe 33 min. Center a little bit jiggly.